Add two new configurable fields to the ValidationConfig struct, following the exact pattern established by the existing four fields (max_title_length, max_description_length, max_story_points, max_error_message_length).

Each field needs three constants (MIN, MAX, DEFAULT), a struct field, a default value, and a bounds check in validate().

**BUG FIX 1: Add `Copy` derive to ValidationConfig.**
The struct only contains `usize` and `i32` fields (all `Copy` types), so it should derive `Copy` alongside `Clone`. This avoids unnecessary `.clone()` calls and prevents future breakage if someone adds a non-Copy field without noticing.

**BUG FIX 2: Name config-bound constants clearly.**
Constants that define the min/max bounds for the configurable value must NOT be confused with user-facing validation limits. Use `MIN_CONFIGURABLE_*` / `MAX_CONFIGURABLE_*` prefix to make intent obvious.

**File**: backend/crates/pm-config/src/validation_config.rs

Change the struct derive:

Before:
```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Deserialize)]
pub struct ValidationConfig {
```

After:
```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, Deserialize)]
pub struct ValidationConfig {
```

Add the new constants after the existing ones (after line 20, before the time entry constants):

```rust
// Config bounds: min/max values the max_comment_length setting can be set to
pub const MIN_CONFIGURABLE_COMMENT_LENGTH: usize = 1;
pub const MAX_CONFIGURABLE_COMMENT_LENGTH: usize = 50000;
pub const DEFAULT_MAX_COMMENT_LENGTH: usize = 5000;

// Config bounds: min/max values the max_sprint_name_length setting can be set to
pub const MIN_CONFIGURABLE_SPRINT_NAME_LENGTH: usize = 1;
pub const MAX_CONFIGURABLE_SPRINT_NAME_LENGTH: usize = 500;
pub const DEFAULT_MAX_SPRINT_NAME_LENGTH: usize = 100;
```

Add fields to the ValidationConfig struct:

```rust
pub struct ValidationConfig {
    pub max_title_length: usize,
    pub max_description_length: usize,
    pub max_story_points: i32,
    pub max_error_message_length: usize,
    /// Maximum length for comment content
    pub max_comment_length: usize,
    /// Maximum length for sprint names
    pub max_sprint_name_length: usize,
}
```

Add defaults in impl Default:

```rust
impl Default for ValidationConfig {
    fn default() -&amp;gt; Self {
        Self {
            max_title_length: DEFAULT_MAX_TITLE_LENGTH,
            max_description_length: DEFAULT_MAX_DESCRIPTION_LENGTH,
            max_story_points: DEFAULT_MAX_STORY_POINTS,
            max_error_message_length: DEFAULT_MAX_ERROR_MESSAGE_LENGTH,
            max_comment_length: DEFAULT_MAX_COMMENT_LENGTH,
            max_sprint_name_length: DEFAULT_MAX_SPRINT_NAME_LENGTH,
        }
    }
}
```

Add bounds validation in validate():

```rust
if self.max_comment_length &amp;lt; MIN_CONFIGURABLE_COMMENT_LENGTH
