The subscription is unnecessary because `BlockedIndicator` does not own any state. It reads `IsBlocked` and `BlockedByCount` from `DependencyStore` at render time. The parent `KanbanBoard` already re-renders on state changes, which re-renders all visible cards including their `BlockedIndicator`s.

## Implementation

Remove the subscription, handler, `IDisposable` implementation, and `@implements IDisposable` directive. The component becomes a stateless render function.

**Critical**: Cache computed values in `OnParametersSet()` instead of using computed properties. Blazor re-evaluates property getters on every reference during render — using computed properties for `BlockedByCount` would call `DependencyStore.GetBlockingCount()` multiple times per render (once in `BlockedByText`, once in the template conditional). With 108 cards, that doubles the store queries unnecessarily.

