## What

Add a single-item variant of hierarchy computation for use in create/update broadcast paths where we only need data for one modified item.

## Why

When broadcasting a work item create or update, we need hierarchy data for just the modified item — not the entire project. This function delegates to compute_hierarchy_maps and extracts the single entry, keeping traversal logic in one place.

## File

backend/crates/pm-ws/src/handlers/hierarchy.rs (append after compute_hierarchy_maps)

## Implementation

This function reuses compute_hierarchy_maps to avoid duplicating traversal logic. It takes ownership of the HashMap entry via remove() to avoid cloning.

```rust
/// Compute hierarchy for a SINGLE item given all project items.
///
/// Used in create/update broadcast paths. Delegates to
/// compute_hierarchy_maps internally and extracts the entry
/// for the specified item, avoiding logic duplication.
pub fn compute_hierarchy_for_item(items: &[WorkItem], item_id: Uuid) -> HierarchyData {
    let mut maps = compute_hierarchy_maps(items);
    maps.remove(&item_id).unwrap_or_else(|| HierarchyData {
        ancestor_ids: Vec::new(),
        descendant_ids: Vec::new(),
    })
}
```

## Notes

- Uses remove() instead of get() to take ownership without cloning the Vec<String> lists.
- Returns empty HierarchyData if item_id is not found — graceful degradation rather than error.
- unwrap_or_else satisfies the clippy::unwrap_used lint (no panic path).

