## What

After the update transaction completes, fetch all project items and compute hierarchy for the updated item. Pass hierarchy data to both the broadcast and response. For the no-change early return path, compute hierarchy inline before returning.

## Why

When a work item parent changes (reparenting), its ancestor/descendant chains change. The hierarchy must reflect the post-commit state so clients receive accurate data. Computing hierarchy BEFORE the transaction (as previously specified) would return stale parent_id data on reparent operations.

The reviewer correctly identified that placing hierarchy computation before the transaction means `find_by_project` returns the OLD parent_id for the updated item, producing incorrect ancestor/descendant chains.

