## Context

The Update merge is simpler than Create: all fields are already `Option<T>` so there are no required fields to validate. We load TOML, merge with CLI values (CLI wins), and pass to the client. `update_parent` and `version` remain CLI-only.

**Prerequisite:** PONE-211 must be completed first (adds `toml = { workspace = true }` to `pm-cli/Cargo.toml`). This task reuses the `load_work_item_toml` helper defined in PONE-216 which returns `CliClientResult<WorkItemToml>` — `?` propagates load errors to the existing single error handler at the bottom of `main`.

**Important:** `async fn main() -> ExitCode` returns `ExitCode`, **not** `Result`. The `?` operator only works inside a context that returns `Result`. To use it inside the `Update` arm, wrap the entire arm body in `async { ... }.await`. Inside that nested async block `?` propagates to the block's `CliClientResult<Value>`, not to `main()`. This is the same pattern required by the `Create` arm in PONE-216 and the output-phase handler in PONE-213.

**Note on parent_id:** `parent_id` can be populated from the TOML file, but `update_parent` cannot — it defaults to `false`. When an LLM writes `parent_id = "..."` in a TOML file, the field is merged and sent to the server, but the server treats `update_parent=false` as "do not change the parent." The reparenting silently never happens. To surface this before it misleads the caller, emit a warning **only when `parent_id` was actually loaded from TOML** (i.e. the CLI did not supply `--parent-id`) and `update_parent` is not set.

## Implementation

**File:** `backend/crates/pm-cli/src/main.rs`

Replace the `WorkItemCommands::Update` arm. The `load_work_item_toml` helper was added in PONE-216 and returns `CliClientResult<WorkItemToml>`. Wrap the entire arm body in `async { ... }.await` so the `?` on `load_work_item_toml(path).await?` propagates inside the block rather than attempting to propagate from `main()`.

```rust
WorkItemCommands::Update {
    id, title, description, status, priority,
    assignee_id, sprint_id, story_points,
    parent_id, update_parent, position,
    from_toml, version,
} => {
    async {
        let base = if let Some(ref path) = from_toml {
            load_work_item_toml(path).await?  // OK — propagates inside async block, not main()
        } else {
            work_item_commands::WorkItemToml::default()
        };

        // CLI flags take precedence over TOML values for all optional fields
        let title        = title.or(base.title);
        let description  = description.or(base.description);
        let status       = status.or(base.status);
        let priority     = priority.or(base.priority);
        let assignee_id  = assignee_id.or(base.assignee_id);
        let sprint_id    = sprint_id.or(base.sprint_id);
        let story_points = story_points.or(base.story_points);
        let position     = position.or(base.position);

        // Validate story_points range (0-100) after merge.
        // TOML loading bypasses any CLI-level validator, so we must check here.
        if let Some(sp) = story_points {
            if !(0..=100).contains(&sp) {
                return Err(ClientError::Validation {
                    message: format!(
                        "story_points must be between 0 and 100, got {}", sp
                    ),
                });
            }
        }

        // Capture CLI state BEFORE the or() merge so the warning condition is accurate:
        // the warning should only fire when TOML actually won the merge — not when the
        // CLI supplied --parent-id and the TOML value was silently discarded.
        let cli_had_parent = parent_id.is_some();
        let toml_parent_id = base.parent_id;
        let parent_id = parent_id.or(toml_parent_id.clone());
        if !cli_had_parent && toml_parent_id.is_some() && !update_parent {
            eprintln!(
                "Warning: parent_id was loaded from the TOML file but --update-parent is not set. \
                 Parent will NOT be changed. Add --update-parent to the CLI command to reparent."
            );
        }
        // update_parent and version are CLI-only — not read from TOML

        client
            .update_work_item(
                &id,
                title.as_deref(),
                description.as_deref(),
                status.as_deref(),
                priority.as_deref(),
                assignee_id.as_deref(),
                sprint_id.as_deref(),
                story_points,
                parent_id.as_deref(),
                update_parent,
                position,
                version,
            )
            .await
    }
    .await
}
```

Note: the `eprintln!` for the parent_id warning is intentional — it is a **warning**, not an error. Execution continues and the command succeeds. This is the correct use of `eprintln!` to stderr for advisory messages that do not affect the exit code.

