Modify build_work_items_list_response to accept both the response items AND the full project item set (both borrowed), computing hierarchy from the full set. Add a debug assertion to enforce the subset contract at development time.

## Why

The reviewer correctly identified that computing hierarchy from the `work_items` parameter is unsafe: if a future caller passes a filtered list (e.g., only in_progress items), hierarchy chains would be incomplete. Create/update handlers already fetch the full project set — the list response must be consistent.

Additionally, the reviewer identified that the function only reads work_items (iterates via `.iter()`), so taking ownership via `Vec<WorkItem>` is wasteful. Use `&[WorkItem]` for both parameters.

The reviewer also flagged that callers passing `&work_items, &work_items` (same variable twice) is a type safety hole — a future developer could filter `work_items` but forget to keep the unfiltered copy for the second parameter. The `debug_assert!` catches this at dev time.

