## PONE-53: Add keyboard shortcuts for markdown

### Requires JSInterop module
Create `frontend/ProjectManagement.Components/wwwroot/js/markdownEditor.js`:

```javascript
export function getSelectionRange(textarea) {
    return {
        start: textarea.selectionStart,
        end: textarea.selectionEnd,
        text: textarea.value.substring(textarea.selectionStart, textarea.selectionEnd)
    };
}

export function insertAtCursor(textarea, prefix, suffix, isBlock) {
    const start = textarea.selectionStart;
    const end = textarea.selectionEnd;
    const selected = textarea.value.substring(start, end);
    const before = textarea.value.substring(0, start);
    const after = textarea.value.substring(end);

    let insertion;
    if (isBlock &amp;&amp; start &amp;gt; 0 &amp;&amp; before[before.length - 1] \!== &#x27;\n&#x27;) {
        insertion = &#x27;\n&#x27; + prefix + (selected || &#x27;text&#x27;) + suffix;
    } else {
        insertion = prefix + (selected || &#x27;text&#x27;) + suffix;
    }

    textarea.value = before + insertion + after;

    // Position cursor after prefix, selecting the placeholder/selected text
    const newCursorStart = start + prefix.length + (isBlock &amp;&amp; start &amp;gt; 0 ? 1 : 0);
    const newCursorEnd = newCursorStart + (selected || &#x27;text&#x27;).length;
    textarea.setSelectionRange(newCursorStart, newCursorEnd);
    textarea.focus();

    // Trigger input event so Blazor picks up the change
    textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event(&#x27;input&#x27;, { bubbles: true }));
    textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event(&#x27;change&#x27;, { bubbles: true }));
}
```

### MarkdownEditor keyboard handling (add to @code block)
```csharp
[Inject] private IJSRuntime JS { get; set; } = default\!;
private IJSObjectReference? _jsModule;
private ElementReference _textareaRef;

protected override async Task OnAfterRenderAsync(bool firstRender)
{
    if (firstRender)
    {
        _jsModule = await JS.InvokeAsync&amp;lt;IJSObjectReference&amp;gt;(
            &quot;import&quot;, &quot;./_content/ProjectManagement.Components/js/markdownEditor.js&quot;);
    }
}

private async Task HandleKeyDown(KeyboardEventArgs e)
{
    if (_jsModule is null) return;

    if (e.CtrlKey || e.MetaKey)
    {
        switch (e.Key)
        {
            case &quot;b&quot;: // Bold
                await _jsModule.InvokeVoidAsync(&quot;insertAtCursor&quot;, _textareaRef, &quot;**&quot;, &quot;**&quot;, false);
                break;
            case &quot;i&quot;: // Italic
                await _jsModule.InvokeVoidAsync(&quot;insertAtCursor&quot;, _textareaRef, &quot;_&quot;, &quot;_&quot;, false);
                break;
            case &quot;k&quot;: // Link
                await _jsModule.InvokeVoidAsync(&quot;insertAtCursor&quot;, _textareaRef, &quot;[&quot;, &quot;](url)&quot;, false);
                break;
        }
    }
}

public async ValueTask DisposeAsync()
{
    if (_jsModule is not null)
        await _jsModule.DisposeAsync();
}
```

### Key decisions
- JSInterop is required because Blazor cannot access textarea.selectionStart/End from C#
- Module loaded lazily on first render, disposed on component teardown
- Ctrl+B/I/K match GitHub/VS Code conventions; Cmd variants handled via e.MetaKey for macOS

### Verification
Run: `just build-cs-components`
Then test Ctrl+B, Ctrl+I, Ctrl+K in the editor textarea.

