## Problem

Every `BlockedIndicator` component (one per card) independently subscribes to `DependencyStore.OnChanged`. When dependencies change, all 108 indicators call `InvokeAsync(StateHasChanged)` individually — that is **108 independent re-render requests** per dependency event.

### Current Code (`BlockedIndicator.razor:23-36`)

```csharp
protected override void OnInitialized()
{
    DependencyStore.OnChanged += HandleChanged;
}

private void HandleChanged()
{
    InvokeAsync(StateHasChanged);   // × 108 components
}

public void Dispose()
{
    DependencyStore.OnChanged -= HandleChanged;
}
```

This is unnecessary because the parent `KanbanBoard` already re-renders on state changes, which re-renders all visible cards (and their `BlockedIndicator`s). The indicator does not maintain its own state — it just reads from `DependencyStore.IsBlocked()` and `DependencyStore.GetBlockingCount()` at render time.

## Solution

Remove the subscription, handler, and `IDisposable` implementation entirely. The component becomes a **pure render function** — it reads from `DependencyStore` during the parent's render cycle and displays the result.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `BlockedIndicator` no longer subscribes to `DependencyStore.OnChanged`
- [ ] `BlockedIndicator` no longer implements `IDisposable`
- [ ] Blocked status still displays correctly on cards
- [ ] `just build-frontend` compiles
- [ ] `just test-frontend` passes
